UP SAMPLING

import cv2
image=cv2.imread("C:/Users/User/Documents/Python Scripts/sun.jpg")
print("size of image before pyrUp: ",image.shape)
cv2.imshow("im1",image)
cv2.waitKey(0)
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
image=cv2.pyrUp(image)
print("size of image after pyrUp: ",image.shape)
cv2.imshow("UpSample",image)
cv2.waitKey(0)
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
OUTPUT:
size of image before pyrUp:  (183, 275, 3)
size of image after pyrUp:  (366, 550, 3)
IMAGE BECOMES LARGE

DOWN SAMPLING 

import cv2
image=cv2.imread("C:/Users/User/Documents/Python Scripts/sun.jpg")
print("size of image before pyrDown: ",image.shape)
cv2.imshow("im1",image)
cv2.waitKey(0)
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
image=cv2.pyrDown(image)
print("size of image after pyrDown: ",image.shape)
cv2.imshow("DownSample",image)
cv2.waitKey(0)
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
OUTPUT:
size of image before pyrDown:  (183, 275, 3)
size of image after pyrDown:  (92, 138, 3)
IMAGE BECOMES SAMLLER
